leaving your friends, and nobody wants to do that.  We want to make the social
connections between users independent of the particular websites they might use
to send messages and share photos.  This will free users to choose their social
media app for its features (like privacy!) and to change that choice at any time
without having to give up existing connections with their friends and family.]]></description><link>http://DSNP-org.gihub.io/why-do-we-need-the-dsnp/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">Ghost__Post__60c110182982200001275353</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Claire Olmstead]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 09 Jun 2021 19:02:11 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Existing social media sites are all silos that trap users—leaving Facebook means leaving your friends, and nobody wants to do that.  We want to make the social connections between users independent of the particular websites they might use to send messages and share photos.  This will free users to choose their social media app for its features (like privacy!) and to change that choice at any time without having to give up existing connections with their friends and family.</p>]]></content:encoded></item></channel></rss>